cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on using computer vision techniques to extract meta features from body gestures for affective computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with psychological distress and personality measures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of video recordings and the development of a new dataset suggest that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also uses machine learning techniques for prediction tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with natural language-like representations of body language, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
